Articles.Content:
So, this seems to be a place I can store my creations in case my disks die or something, right? If anyone else benefits from it, all the better! Questions are welcome... comments, complaints not so much.

I'll start with a replica of a SU-27: Capable of "cobra maneuvre", has dinky missiles and bombs that dont work in recent versions because squad doesn't understand how pylons work, and have screwed up the fuel transfer. Requires tweakscale and kOS (the kOS part can be removed with no noticable effect)

Made with 0.90, but updated in 1.1.3.

Spoiler

ship = Sukoi 27
version = 1.1.3
description = Requires tweakscale only for the nose wheel.¨Has removable Mechjeb, kOS.¨¨The cockpits look a bit gimpy but it's the best we can do with stock parts.¨¨Rockets dont fly straight - the pylons weigh a tonne and seperate with the rocket. Thats not how pylons work, Squad!¨Also since they loveed up the fuel feed, they immediately run out of fuel.¨¨Can do the Cobra maneuvre pretty well.¨¨Can carry more fuel, but current load is based on reported range.
type = SPH
size = 10.72165,5.958702,15.93975

// numbers, although those are usually fighter jets or rockets
// (or things that shouldnt fly at all). However, if it does start
// to wobble all over the place, just slow down! It'll get you
// there eventually.
// I guess its technically not a *space*plane autopilot, its just
// an aeroplane autopilot.
//
// It might be possible to make this work for rockets, but will
// require MUCH more precise loops. Let me know if you try,
// I have a suspicion that doing so will destroy the large range
// of aircraft this works for though - at best you'll end up with
// one set of values that work for rockets, and another for planes.
//
// Its possible to put the control loops in when () loops, so you
// can also run some other script, but so far its not optimized
// much, and ive found that activating all 3 controllers causes
// instruction limit errors. The vnav one is particularly code
// heavy.
//
// might be possible to modify wing leveller to help rnav (bank into
// turns), but not currently a goal.
//

// default altitude hold setting
set alt_setting to 5000.


clearscreen.
print "---Spaceplane Autopilot---".
print " ".
print "Press 5 for autothrottle (speed hold)".
print "Press 6 to reduce vs hold, 7 to increase.".
print "Select a target, and press 8 to enable rnav.".
print "Press 9 to cycle vnav mode".
print "        (off/vs hold/alt hold).".
print "Press 0 to toggle wing leveler.".


SET rollpid TO PIDLOOP(2.0, 0.02, 0.0, -90, 90).
set rollpid:setpoint to 0.
lock roll_error to
//    arccos(vdot(ship:up:vector:normalized,
//    ship:facing:starvector:normalized)) -90.
// dang it, i always forget about vang and it may be faster
// FIXME: this has some kind of wierd bias to it
    vang(ship:up:vector, ship:facing:starvector)-90.
//    local r1 to vcrs(up:vector,
//        SHIP:FACING:STARVECTOR):normalized.
//    local h to vang(r1, east:vector).
//    if (r1:y) > 0.0 set h to 360 -h.
    
// vnav 'types'
set VNAVOFF to 0.
set VSHOLD to 2.
set ALTHOLD to 1.
//
set vnavmode to VNAVOFF.

set vs_target to 0.
set evholdpid to PIDLOOP(0.10, 0.0009, 0.050, -1, 1).
set evholdpid:setpoint to 0.

SET altholdpid TO PIDLOOP(0.2, 0.002, 0.09, -100, 100).
set altholdpid:setpoint to 0.

// fix up broken SHIP:HEADING.
set northpole to  latlng(90, 0).
lock SHIPHDG to mod(360 -northpole:bearing, 360).
// great. no way to tell if a target is set.
// so we have to just clobber it and expect user to (re)set it.
set TARGET to "Sun".
print " ".
print " ".
SET yawpid TO PIDLOOP(1.8, 4.5, 8.1, -45, 45).
set yawpid:setpoint to 0.

set SPEEDSET to 80.
SET pwrpid TO PIDLOOP(0.05, 0.0001, 0.005, 0, 1).
set pwrpid:setpoint to 0.5.

// possibly unnecessary now:
lock aoa to vang(ship:velocity:surface, ship:facing:upvector) -90.
lock pitch_ang to 90 -vang(ship:up:forevector,
        ship:facing:forevector).


function simple_eta {
    parameter dest.

    set Vn to vdot(ship:velocity:surface,
        heading(dest:heading, 0):vector:normalized).
    if (Vn <= 0) return -1.
    // FIXME: geoposition:distance is not great circle.
    return dest:distance /Vn.
}


function print_wl {
    if (AG10) {
        print "wing level enabled (e:" +round(roll_error, 4)
            +", c:" +round(SHIP:CONTROL:ROLL, 4)
            +")                             " at (0,10).
    } else {
        print "wing level disabled"
        +"                                  " at (0,10).
    }
}


function print_vnav {
    if (vnavmode = VNAVOFF) {
        print "vnav disabled "
        +"(" +round(vs_target) +"m/s)                    " at (0,12).
    } else if (vnavmode = ALTHOLD) {
        print "altitude hold " +round(alt_setting)
        +"m (vs: " +round(vs_target, 2) +"m/s)"
        +"                                   " at (0,12).
    } else if (vnavmode = VSHOLD) {
        print "vs hold " +round(vs_target) +"m/s"
        +"m/s (e: " +round(SHIP:VERTICALSPEED -vs_target, 2)
        +"m/s)                                " at (0,12).
    }
}


function print_rnav {
    if ((not HASTARGET) or TARGET = BODY("Sun")) {
        print "Select TARGET for rnav function."
            at(0,14).
        return.
    }
    if (not AG8) {
        print "rnav disabled.                              "
            at(0,14).
        return.
    }

    print "rnav enabled, c: "
        +round(SHIPHDG, 1)    +", e: "
        +round(TARGET:GEOPOSITION:BEARING, 1)
        +"              " at(0,14).
}


on AG10 {
    if not AG10 {
        set SHIP:CONTROL:ROLL to 0.
        print "wing level disabled             " at (0,10).
    }
    preserve.
}
on AG9 {
    if (vnavmode = VNAVOFF) {
        set vnavmode to VSHOLD.
//        evholdpid:reset().
    } else if (vnavmode = VSHOLD) {
        set vnavmode to ALTHOLD.
        if (SHIP:ALTITUDE > 2000)
            set alt_setting to round(SHIP:ALTITUDE/10, 0) *10.
        else set alt_setting to 2000.
//        altholdpid:reset().
//        evholdpid:reset().
    } else if (vnavmode = ALTHOLD) {
        set vnavmode to VNAVOFF.
        set SHIP:CONTROL:PITCH to 0.
    }
    print_vnav().
    preserve.
}
on AG6 {
    set vs_target to vs_target -5.
    preserve.
}
on AG7 {
    set vs_target to vs_target +5.
    preserve.
}
on AG5 {
    if AG5 {
        set SPEEDSET to SHIP:GROUNDSPEED.
        set SHIP:CONTROL:MAINTHROTTLE to
            SHIP:CONTROL:PILOTMAINTHROTTLE.

    } else {
        set SHIP:CONTROL:PILOTMAINTHROTTLE to
            SHIP:CONTROL:MAINTHROTTLE.
        set SHIP:CONTROL:MAINTHROTTLE to 0.
    }
    preserve.
}


//when (round(time:seconds) > last_time) and AG10 then {
function roll_loop {
    if (not AG10) {
        print_wl().
        return.
    }
    local rc to rollpid:update(TIME:SECONDS*10, roll_error/90).
    SET SHIP:CONTROL:ROLL to rc.
    print_wl().
}


function vshold_loop {
//    parameter vs_t to vs_target.
    
    if (vnavmode = VNAVOFF) {
        print_vnav().
        return.
    }

    if (vnavmode = ALTHOLD) {
        set vs_target to altholdpid:update(TIME:SECONDS*10,
            (SHIP:ALTITUDE -alt_setting)).
    }
    
    local vs_e to (SHIP:VERTICALSPEED -vs_target).
    // divide by some sort of random number probably related
    // to how much elevator pitch change causes the vs.
    local pc to evholdpid:update(TIME:SECONDS*10, vs_e/10).
    set SHIP:CONTROL:PITCH to pc.

    print_vnav().
}


function rnav_loop {
    if ((not AG8) or TARGET = BODY("Sun")) {
        SET SHIP:CONTROL:YAW to 0.
        print_rnav().
        return.
    }

    local yaw_c to yawpid:update(TIME:SECONDS*10,
            -TARGET:GEOPOSITION:BEARING).
    SET SHIP:CONTROL:YAW to yaw_c /25.
    
    print_rnav().
    
    local eta to simple_eta(TARGET:GEOPOSITION).
    local secs to eta -floor(eta/60.0) *60.
    print "    eta: " +round(eta/60) +":"
        +round(secs, 1) +"s      " at(0,15).
}

// FIXME: untested.
function pwr_loop {
    if (not AG5)
    {
        print "Autothrottle OFF          " at(0,17).
        return.
    }
    
    local pwr_c to pwrpid:update(TIME:SECONDS*10,
            SHIP:GROUNDSPEED -SPEEDSET).
    set SHIP:CONTROL:MAINTHROTTLE to
        pwr_c.
    
    print "    SPEEDSET: " +round(SPEEDSET, 1)
        +"m/s    "at(0,16).
    print "dS: " +round(SHIP:GROUNDSPEED -SPEEDSET, 1)
         +"m/s   " at(25,16).
    print "pwr_c: " +round(pwr_c, 2) +"       " at(0,17).
    print "MAINTHROTTLE: " +round(SHIP:CONTROL:MAINTHROTTLE, 1)
        +"   " at(0,18).
}

until 0 {
    roll_loop().
    vshold_loop().
    rnav_loop().
    pwr_loop().
        
//    if (defined tgtgeo) print "ETA: " +round(simple_eta(tgtgeo))
//        +"s        " at(0, 26).
    
    wait 0.1.
}
